<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5401712>
    dc:description "FIG. 2. — A-I, photographs of the median areas of the interambulacra, showing the variation in characters that occur: A, Diadema antillarum; B, D. mexicanum; C, D, D. savignyi; E, D. setosum; F, Echinothrix calamaris (brown colour morph); G, E. calamaris (white colour morph); H, E. diadema; I, D. palmeri; J, D. palmeri (whole specimen). Scale bars: A-I, 5 mm; J, 50 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5401712/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5401708>
    dc:description "FIG. 1. — Drawings of the apical systems, showing species specific characters of the periproct and genital plates: A, Diadema antillarum; B, D. ascensionis; C, D. mexicanum; D, D. palmeri; E, D. paucispinum; F, D. savignyi; G, D. setosum; H, Echinothrix calamaris (brown colour morph); I, E. calamaris (white colour morph); J, E. diadema. Scale bars: 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5401708/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

